  "Louie presides over grocery retailer H.Y. Louie and drug store chain London Drugs.",
  "His Vancouver-based holding company H.Y. Louie is the third-largest private firm in British Columbia, with an estimated $4.2 billion in revenue.",
  "His grandfather, Hok Yat Louie, immigrated to Vancouver from China in 1896 and worked as a farm laborer.",
  "Hok Yat eventually saved enough money to open a small general store in the city's Chinatown in 1903.",
  "Louie joined the family business in 1972 and became president in 1987."
